<section class="hero hero--inner">
  <div class="plan-grid">
    <div class="hero__content">
      <span class="hero__eyebrow">Pricing</span>
      <h1 class="hero__title">
        <span>One plan.</span>
        <span class="hero__title-muted">One account.</span>
        <span>One billing home.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="hero__copy">
        Start with a 7-day trial, upgrade through Stripe, and keep the same entitlement across the Voxlane
        website and the macOS app.
      </p>

      <div class="badge-row">
        <span class="pill">7-day trial</span>
        <span class="pill">Monthly billing</span>
        <span class="pill">Direct macOS delivery</span>
      </div>

      <p class="hero__caption">
        Billing is hosted on the website, the backend owns the access state, and the desktop app refreshes the
        same entitlement as soon as the webhook sync completes.
      </p>
    </div>

    <aside class="plan-card">
      <span class="plan-card__eyebrow">Voxlane Pro</span>
      <div class="plan-card__price"><%= AppConfig.stripe_price_label %></div>
      <p>
        Everything in the Voxlane billing flow is centered around a single user identity, not a fragile device receipt.
      </p>

      <ul class="checklist">
        <li>Account-based trial that survives device switches</li>
        <li>Hosted Stripe checkout with a self-serve billing portal</li>
        <li>Shared entitlement for the website and macOS client</li>
        <li>Release notes and Sparkle updates from the same backend</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="button-row">
        <% if authenticated? %>
          <%= button_to "Open Stripe checkout",
            checkout_path(
              success_url: account_url(checkout: "success"),
              cancel_url: pricing_url(checkout: "cancelled")
            ),
            method: :post,
            class: "button button--primary" %>
          <a class="button button--secondary" href="<%= account_path %>">Manage account</a>
        <% else %>
          <a class="button button--primary" href="<%= login_path %>">Sign in to start trial</a>
          <a class="button button--secondary" href="<%= install_instructions_path(downloadLink: AppConfig.app_download_url) %>">Download app</a>
        <% end %>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="section-head">
    <span class="kicker">Included</span>
    <h2>Everything the website needs to support the app is already in the plan flow.</h2>
    <p>
      This page is no longer acting like a makeshift homepage. It is focused on what users actually need to
      understand before they upgrade.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="grid grid--2">
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Trial that follows the user</h3>
      <p>Start once, sign in again anywhere, and keep the same trial state tied to the account.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Checkout hosted on the web</h3>
      <p>Upgrade through Stripe without routing billing through the App Store.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Entitlement sync for desktop</h3>
      <p>The app reads the same backend access record the website uses for pricing and billing state.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Release delivery included</h3>
      <p>Direct downloads, Sparkle appcasts, and release notes are already part of the same backend surface.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="section-head">
    <span class="kicker">Flow</span>
    <h2>What happens after a user decides to upgrade.</h2>
    <p>
      The billing story stays simple because the site, database, and app are all reading from the same source of truth.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="grid grid--4">
    <article class="card">
      <span class="pill pill--ghost">Step 1</span>
      <h3>Sign in</h3>
      <p>Use Google or email and password to establish the web session and account context.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <span class="pill pill--ghost">Step 2</span>
      <h3>Open checkout</h3>
      <p>Voxlane creates the Stripe checkout session and hands off to hosted billing.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <span class="pill pill--ghost">Step 3</span>
      <h3>Sync entitlement</h3>
      <p>Stripe webhooks reconcile subscription state into the backend entitlement record.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <span class="pill pill--ghost">Step 4</span>
      <h3>Refresh the app</h3>
      <p>The desktop client reads the updated access state and continues without receipt drift.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--tight">
  <div class="plan-grid">
    <div>
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="kicker">Shipping</span>
        <h2>Need the latest build details before you decide?</h2>
        <p>
          Release notes are published from the same backend, so users can see what changed before downloading.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <article class="card card--accent">
      <h3>Latest release</h3>
      <p>See the currently published Voxlane build and the notes Sparkle will link to in-app.</p>
      <div class="button-row">
        <a class="button button--primary" href="<%= release_notes_path %>">View release notes</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
